    <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="31" layoutY="73" styleClass="info" text="With CD-HIT-EST you can search for clusters of similar sequences from two datasets.&#10;The program first takes the sequences from the first dataset and marks them &#10;as reference burst sequences. Then it reads the second dataset and assigns &#10;its sequence to clusters from the first dataset. In the output file, each cluster &#10;then contains exactly one sequence from the first dataset and the remaining &#10;sequences from the second dataset. In my implementation, only the PQS vicinities &#10;cluster. The PQS are written to the files only after the clustering is completed.&#10;&#10;Input:&#10;   First Dataset&#10;- combined left and right areas of found PQS (pqsareas output)&#10;- found PQS (pqsfinder output)&#10;&#10;   Second Dataset&#10;- combined left and right areas of found PQS (pqsareas output)&#10;- found PQS (pqsfinder output)&#10;&#10;- output directory + output name&#10;- additional parameters&#10;&#10;Output:&#10;- FASTA file of clusters of similar sequences &#10;(individual line sequences are PQS with left and right areas)&#10;&#10;Click on the button &quot;Open Doc&quot; to read the complete documentation. If nothing &#10;happens, you can find the documentation in the ... / resources / documentation &#10;folder in the application directory.">
        <font>
            <Font size="15.0" />
        </font>
    </TextArea>
    <Button layoutX="643.0" layoutY="17.0" mnemonicParsing="false" onAction="#open_doc" text="Open Doc">
